 {"id":"charmed_rust-i3b","title":"[Theme] Add Style::from_theme() constructor","description":"## Parent Epic
charmed_rust-eli: [Theme] Add theming/color scheme support to lipgloss

## Objective
Add a `Style::from_theme()` constructor that creates styles pre-configured with theme colors, enabling seamless integration between the theming system and lipgloss's existing Style API.

## Detailed Requirements

### 1. Core Constructor API
Implement constructors that accept theme and color slots:

```rust
use lipgloss::{Style, Theme, ColorSlot};

impl Style {
    /// Create a style with foreground color from theme
    pub fn from_theme(theme: &Theme, slot: ColorSlot) -> Self {
        Style::new().foreground(theme.get(slot))
    }

    /// Create a style with both foreground and background from theme
    pub fn from_theme_colors(
        theme: &Theme,
        fg: ColorSlot,
        bg: ColorSlot,
    ) -> Self {
        Style::new()
            .foreground(theme.get(fg))
            .background(theme.get(bg))
    }

    /// Create a style using a theme's semantic role
    pub fn from_theme_role(theme: &Theme, role: ThemeRole) -> Self {
        match role {
            ThemeRole::Primary => Style::new()
                .foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Primary)),
            ThemeRole::Success => Style::new()
                .foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Success)),
            ThemeRole::Warning => Style::new()
                .foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Warning)),
            ThemeRole::Error => Style::new()
                .foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Error)),
            ThemeRole::Muted => Style::new()
                .foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Muted)),
            ThemeRole::Inverted => Style::new()
                .foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Background))
                .background(theme.get(ColorSlot::Foreground)),
        }
    }
}

/// Semantic roles for quick style creation
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy)]
pub enum ThemeRole {
    Primary,
    Success,
    Warning,
    Error,
    Muted,
    Inverted,
}
```

### 2. Builder Pattern Extensions
Extend the existing Style builder to accept theme colors:

```rust
impl Style {
    /// Set foreground from theme color slot
    pub fn foreground_slot(self, theme: &Theme, slot: ColorSlot) -> Self {
        self.foreground(theme.get(slot))
    }

    /// Set background from theme color slot
    pub fn background_slot(self, theme: &Theme, slot: ColorSlot) -> Self {
        self.background(theme.get(slot))
    }

    /// Set border color from theme color slot
    pub fn border_foreground_slot(self, theme: &Theme, slot: ColorSlot) -> Self {
        self.border_foreground(theme.get(slot))
    }

    /// Set border background from theme color slot
    pub fn border_background_slot(self, theme: &Theme, slot: ColorSlot) -> Self {
        self.border_background(theme.get(slot))
    }
}
```

### 3. Convenience Presets for Common UI Patterns
Provide factory methods for common UI element styles:

```rust
impl Style {
    /// Create a button-like style from theme
    pub fn button_from_theme(theme: &Theme) -> Self {
        Style::new()
            .foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Background))
            .background(theme.get(ColorSlot::Primary))
            .padding_horizontal(2)
            .padding_vertical(1)
            .bold(true)
    }

    /// Create an error message style from theme
    pub fn error_from_theme(theme: &Theme) -> Self {
        Style::new()
            .foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Error))
            .bold(true)
    }

    /// Create a muted/secondary text style from theme
    pub fn muted_from_theme(theme: &Theme) -> Self {
        Style::new()
            .foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Muted))
            .italic(true)
    }

    /// Create a highlighted/selected item style from theme
    pub fn selected_from_theme(theme: &Theme) -> Self {
        Style::new()
            .foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Foreground))
            .background(theme.get(ColorSlot::Selection))
    }

    /// Create a bordered panel style from theme
    pub fn panel_from_theme(theme: &Theme) -> Self {
        Style::new()
            .border(Border::rounded())
            .border_foreground(theme.get(ColorSlot::Border))
            .padding(1)
    }
}
```

### 4. Usage Examples

```rust
use lipgloss::{Style, ThemePreset};

fn main() {
    let theme = ThemePreset::Dracula.to_theme();

    // Simple themed style
    let title = Style::from_theme(&theme, ColorSlot::Primary)
        .bold(true)
        .padding_horizontal(1);

    // Using builder extensions
    let warning = Style::new()
        .foreground_slot(&theme, ColorSlot::Warning)
        .background_slot(&theme, ColorSlot::Surface0)
        .padding(1);

    // Using preset factories
    let button = Style::button_from_theme(&theme);
    let error_msg = Style::error_from_theme(&theme);

    println!("{}", title.render("Welcome"));
    println!("{}", warning.render("Caution: Low disk space"));
    println!("{}", button.render(" OK "));
    println!("{}", error_msg.render("Error: File not found"));
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `Style::from_theme(theme, slot)` creates style with foreground color
- [ ] `Style::from_theme_colors(theme, fg, bg)` sets both colors
- [ ] `Style::from_theme_role(theme, role)` provides semantic shortcuts
- [ ] Builder methods `foreground_slot()`, `background_slot()` work correctly
- [ ] All border color methods have theme-aware variants
- [ ] Factory methods for common UI patterns (button, error, muted, panel)
- [ ] Methods are ergonomic and follow existing Style API conventions
- [ ] Full documentation with examples for each method
- [ ] Unit tests cover all constructors and builder methods

## Implementation Notes
- Maintain immutability: all methods return new Style instances
- Consider generic `impl Into<Color>` for flexibility
- Theme reference should not be stored in Style (styles remain theme-agnostic)
- This is a "snapshot" approach - styles capture theme colors at creation time
- For dynamic theme switching, see charmed_rust-uvb (ThemedStyle wrapper)

## Logging Requirements
- DEBUG: Log style creation with theme slot: `style.from_theme`, `color_slot`
- TRACE: Log individual color resolutions during style building
- No INFO/WARN logs needed for this feature

