 {"id":"charmed_rust-idw4","title":"Implement Model trait for textarea component","description":"## Overview
Add Model trait implementation to the textarea component for multi-line text editing.

## Model Implementation

### init()
- Initialize with empty or provided text
- Set cursor position
- Return focus command or Cmd::none()

### update(msg)
Handle these messages:
- `KeyMsg` - Text input and navigation
- `InsertCharMsg(char)` - Insert character at cursor
- `DeleteCharMsg` - Delete character
- `InsertLineMsg` - Insert new line (Enter)
- `MoveCursorMsg(Direction)` - Move cursor
- `SetValueMsg(String)` - Replace all text
- `FocusMsg` / `BlurMsg` - Focus management
- `PasteMsg(String)` - Paste text

Return commands:
- Cursor blink command when focused
- Cmd::none() for most edits

### view()
- Render text with line numbers (optional)
- Show cursor at current position
- Handle line wrapping
- Apply styling for focused/blurred state

## Messages
```rust
pub enum TextAreaMsg {
    Key(KeyEvent),
    InsertChar(char),
    DeleteChar,
    InsertLine,
    MoveCursor(Direction),
    SetValue(String),
    Focus,
    Blur,
    Paste(String),
}
```

